<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="289" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="0.[146,1431,1705,1912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[146,452,1706,1731]" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">Distribution and ecology:</emphasis>
—This new species is only known from Jingxi Xian in southwestern 
<collectingRegion box="[1240,1431,1706,1731]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">Guangxi Zhuang</collectingRegion>
Autonomous Region, 
<collectingCountry box="[391,461,1743,1768]" name="China" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">China</collectingCountry>
, that borders northern 
<collectingCountry box="[711,810,1743,1768]" name="Vietnam" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
. It grows in valleys on shaded rocky limestone slopes at 
<quantity box="[146,273,1779,1804]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="8.8" metricValueMin="8.2" pageId="0" pageNumber="289" unit="m" value="850.0" valueMax="880.0" valueMin="820.0">820–880 m</quantity>
altitude.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[146,1431,1705,1912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[193,494,1815,1840]" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">Taxonomic relationships:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. R. Lin &amp; J. C. Yang" authorityYear="2014" box="[522,750,1815,1839]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="289" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis box="[522,750,1815,1839]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">Aspidistra tenuifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wan &amp; Huang (1987: 220)" authorityName="Wan &amp; Huang" authorityPageNumber="220" authorityYear="1987" box="[894,1354,1815,1840]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="289" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearifolia">
<emphasis box="[894,1050,1815,1839]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">A. linearifolia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wan, Yu &amp; Huang, C. - C." box="[1057,1354,1815,1840]" pageId="0" pageNumber="289" pagination="217 - 224" refId="ref2035" refString="Wan, Yu &amp; Huang, C. - C. (1987) New species of the genus Aspidistra from Guangxi. Guihaia 7: 217 - 224." type="journal article" year="1987">Wan &amp; Huang (1987: 220)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Tillich" authorityName="Tillich" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="289" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">A. alata</emphasis>
Tillich
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Tillich, H. J. &amp; Averyanov, L. V. &amp; Dzu, N. V." box="[329,618,1851,1876]" pageId="0" pageNumber="289" pagination="335 - 344" refId="ref1865" refString="Tillich, H. J., Averyanov, L. V. &amp; Dzu, N. V. (2007) Six new species of Aspidistra (Ruscaceae) from northern Vietnam. Blumea 52: 335 - 344. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3767 / 000651907 x 609070" type="journal article" year="2007">
Tillich 
<emphasis box="[414,473,1851,1875]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">et al.</emphasis>
(2007: 336)
</bibRefCitation>
with linear leaves, perigone campanulate and dark purple. A detailed comparison to distinguish the three species is presented in 
<tableCitation box="[803,886,1887,1912]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="3.[163,242,154,175]" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphological comparison of Aspidistra tenuifolia with A. linearifolia and A. alata." pageId="0" pageNumber="289">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
